window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>Can a love potion help her find real love—or just make her see what’s been there all along?</p> <p>Ally Hawkins has never had a Valentine’s Day date—but this is her year. She can feel it in her endlessly optimistic heart. So when she stumbles upon a love potion at a county fair, she figures…why not? It’s silly, it’s smelly, and she’s a grown woman. But then—bam—the very guy she’s been crushing on asks her to lunch. Coincidence? She thinks not.</p> <p>But while Ally’s busy swooning, her office BFF Josh Wise starts acting weird. Distant. Not his usual flirty, funny, charming self. And Ally realizes she might miss him more than she expected. Maybe the potion isn’t magic at all, maybe it’s just opening her eyes.</p> <p>Now she’ll have to figure out what (or who) she really wants…before the spell wears off for good.</p>"; 
